HEADWORD: Subtrahend
<hw>Sub"tra*hend`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subtrahendus</ets> that is to be subtracted, p.fut.pess. of
<ets>subtrahere</ets>. See <er>Subtract</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>The sum or number to be subtracted, or taken from another (the
<contr>minuend</contr>) to find the <contr>difference</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtranslucent</ent>⟦br⟧
